cs351.core

Interface Level

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ZombieLevel

    public interface Level
    A Level object represents the initial state of a World. When a call to reset is made, a Level should clear the contents of the given World and then set it back to a starting state.
    Author:
    Justin Hall

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void destroy()
      Tells the level that it is done and should clear out any now-dead references it is holding onto.
      void initWorld(World world, Engine engine)
      This should clear out the contents of the given World and then reinitialize it to represent the starting point of whatever Level is being created.
